Former President, Chartered Institute of Taxation of Nigeria, Dame Olajumoke Simplice, has urged female tax professionals to put in their best to achieve their goals. She spoke during the Society of Women in Taxation, Lagos State Chapter’s catch up event in Lagos on Saturday, The female professionals also celebrating the association’s 12 years of existence She said, ‘God has given us that power that is why He created us to multi task. For us to achieve as women, we must persevere, endure, you must be bold and have the capacity to get to the top. “What you want to do, put your heart to it and you will achieve. Mentor other women and teach your children the way of the Lord.” She also said it was important for the upcoming generation to advance their rights. The State Coordinator, SWIT Lagos Chapter, Mrs Cecelia Odibo, said the event was a time to meet, greet and hug each other. She said the group had always interacted through the WhatsApp but did not have the opportunity to come together due to the COVID-19 restrictions. She said, “We felt we should come together to celebrate ourselves, not only relating on WhatsApp. We have a lot of dignitaries on the WhatsApp group. “This is one of the reasons we decided to organise this session to know ourselves. “We will also be celebrating our 12th anniversary as we are about moving from our primary stage to our secondary stage.” The President, CITN, Adesina Adedayo, commended the female professionals for being proactive. Copyright PUNCH All rights reserved. This material, and other digital content on this website, may not be reproduced, published, broadcast, rewritten or redistributed in whole or in part without prior express written permission from PUNCH. Contact: theeditor@punchng.com